20according%20to%20Morgan%20Stanley's%20top%20economist.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESeth%20Carpenter%20said%20Wednesday%20that%20he%20believes%20the%20Federal%20Reserve%20is%20near%20to%20achieving%20a%20so-called%20%26quot%3Bsoft%20landing%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%93%20where%20it%20manages%20to%20bring%20down%20inflation%20without%20causing%20a%20spike%20in%20unemployment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20wouldn't%20say%20that%20we've%20discarded%20it%20wholesale%20%E2%80%93%C2%A0there's%20always%20a%20risk%2C%26quot%3B%20Carpenter%2C%20who%20is%20the%20bank's%20global%20chief%20economist%2C%20told%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fwatch%3Fv%3DFnAy5oJfKjo%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EBloomberg%20TV%2C%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0referring%20to%20the%20risk%20of%20a%20recession.%20%26quot%3BAs%20I%20like%20to%20say%2C%20bad%20things%20happen%20to%20good%20economies%20all%20the%20time.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BBut%20since%20the%20beginning%20of%20this%20hiking%20cycle%20we've%20tried%20to%20say%20'a%20soft%20landing%20is%20the%20most%20likely%20outcome%2C%20the%20economy%20is%20not%20going%20to%20go%20into%20recession'%20as%20a%20base%20case%20forecast%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20added.%20%26quot%3BSo%20far%2C%20that%20view%20here%20has%20come%20true.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Fed%20started%20hiking%20interest%20rates%20in%20March%202022%20%E2%80%93%C2%A0and%20inflation%20has%20since%20fallen%20from%20four-decade%20highs%20to%20just%203.2%25%20as%20of%20last%20month.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDespite%20doomsayers'%20warnings%20earlier%20this%20year%2C%20its%20aggressive%20tightening%20campaign%20is%20yet%20to%20crater%20the%20labor%20market.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20US%20unemployment%20rate%20is%20still%20hovering%20below%203.5%25%20%E2%80%93%20and%20Morgan%20Stanley%20expects%20the%20August%20Non-Farm%20Payrolls%20report%2C%20set%20to%20be%20released%20Friday%2C%20to%20show%20the%20economy%20added%20155%2C000%20more%20jobs%20this%20month.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20growth%20has%20remained%20resilient%20%E2%80%93%C2%A0with%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fapnews.com%2Farticle%2Feconomy-gdp-inflation-federal-reserve-jobs-growth-8934ebcac23acdfef69089db2942f6d6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethe%20economy%20expanding%202.1%25%20between%20April%20and%20June%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20according%20to%20a%20government%20estimate%20Wednesday.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere's%20definitely%20a%20slowdown%2C%20a%20soft%20landing%20%E2%80%93%20but%20boy%2C%20the%20data%20are%20surprising%20to%20the%20upside%2C%20in%20very%20stark%20contrast%20to%20the%20other%20side%20of%20the%20world%2C%26quot%3B%20Carpenter%20told%20Bloomberg%2C%20comparing%20the%20US%20to%20China%2C%20which%20is%20suffering%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchina-economy-crash-recession-growth-retail-sales-inflation-deflation-covid-2023-7%5C%22%3Emajor%20economic%20headache%3C%2Fa%3E%20after%20lifting%20three%20years%20of%20harsh%20zero-COVID%20lockdowns%20at%20the%20end%20of%20last%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECarpenter%20is%20not%20the%20only%20Wall%20Street%20strategist%20who's%20feeling%20optimistic%20right%20now%20%E2%80%93%20with%20other%20big%20banks%20including%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bloomberg.com%2Fnews%2Farticles%2F2023-08-02%2Fbofa-joins-fed-in-reversing-recession-call-amid-growing-optimism%5C%22%3EBank%20of%20America%3C%2Fa%3E%20revising%20their%20outlooks%20for%20the%20US%20economy%20in%20recent%20months.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20his%20own%20company's%20top%20stock-picker%20isn't%20so%20cheerful.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarkets.businessinsider.com%2Fnews%2Fstocks%2Fstock-market-outlook-ai-chatgpt-cooling-inflation-earnings-morgan-stanley-2023-7%5C%22%3EMorgan%20Stanley%20CIO%20Mike%20Wilson%3C%2Fa%3E%20said%20last%20month%20that%20he%20expects%20the%20benchmark%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarkets.businessinsider.com%2Findex%2Fs%26