he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELocal%20residents%20delight%20in%20narrating%20Asrar%E2%80%99s%20%E2%80%98miracles%E2%80%99%20which%20are%20believed%20to%20have%20attracted%20people%20of%20all%20faiths%20to%20the%20Sufi%20fold%20of%20Islam.%20At%20a%20young%20age%2C%20Asrar%2C%20who%20is%20the%20direct%20descendant%20of%20Abdul%20Qadir%20Gilani%2C%20a%20widely%20respected%20Hanbali%20scholar%20from%20Iran%20and%20the%20founder%20of%20Qadiriyya%20sect%20of%20Sufi%20Islam%2C%20commanded%20the%20respect%20of%20the%20people%20of%20Kishtwar%20with%20his%20humility%20and%20miracles.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOne%20popular%20story%20has%20it%20that%20Shah%20Asrar%20brought%20to%20life%20the%20only%20dead%20son%20of%20his%20friend%20and%20a%20Hindu%20resident%20of%20Kishtwar%20merely%20by%20nudging%20him%20with%20his%20walking%20cane%20while%20chanting%20some%20Quranic%20verses.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CHe%20granted%20eyesight%20to%20the%20blind%2C%20made%20walls%20move%2C%20and%20cured%20people%20afflicted%20by%20deadly%20diseases%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20Haji%20Mushtaq%20Ahmad%20Shah%2C%20who%20lives%20in%20the%20shrine%E2%80%99s%20neighbourhood.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMushtaq%20Shah%2C%20a%20descendent%20of%20Shah%20Farid-ud-Din%20Baghdadi%2C%20is%20the%20custodian%20of%20dozens%20of%20precious%2017th-century%20manuscripts%20written%20in%20Persian%2C%20Arabic%20and%20Kurdish%20languages%20which%20detail%20the%20travels%20of%20Baghdadi%2C%20his%20poetry%20and%20a%20charter%20of%20lineage%20of%20Sufi%20saints%20who%20are%20direct%20descendants%20of%20Prophet%20Mohammad%2C%20Islam%E2%80%99s%20most%20revered%20prophet.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F31134336%2FIMG_4919.jpeg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F31134336%2FIMG_4919.jpeg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F31134336%2FIMG_4919-300x225.jpeg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F31134336%2FIMG_4919-1024x768.jpeg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-670835%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22900%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EMushtaq%20Ahmad%20Shah%2C%20a%20descendent%20of%20Shah%20Asrar%2C%20has%20built%20a%20double-storied%20structure%20adjacent%20to%20the%20main%20shrine%20which%20is%20home%20to%20many%20precious%20relics%20and%20manuscripts.%20Photo%3A%20Jehangir%20Ali%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20double-storied%20structure%20built%20by%20Shah%20adjacent%20to%20the%20shrine%20also%20houses%20the%20personal%20belongings%20of%20Shah%20Asrar%2C%20including%20a%20strand%20of%20his%20hair%2C%20a%20bowl%20made%20of%20fishbone%20which%20has%20Quranic%20verses%20inscribed%20on%20it%2C%20a%20walking%20cane%2C%20a%20sword%20and%20a%20cap%20among%20others.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20relics%20of%20Kishtwar%E2%80%99s%20syncretic%20past%20are%20displayed%20every%20year%20during%20the%20annual%20festival%20of%20Shah%20Asrar%20in%20November%20when%20thousands%20of%20people%2C%20including%20Hindus%20and%20Sikhs%2C%20converge%20in%20the%20town%20to%20pay%20their%20respect%20to%20their%20beloved%20saint.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20annual%20festival%20of%20Baghdadi%2C%20Shah%20Asrar%E2%80%99s%20father%2C%20is%20celebrated%20in%20June.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CSaints%20don%E2%80%99t%20belong%20to%20one%20religion%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20Ramesh%20Thakur%2C%20a%20resident%20of%20Kishtwar%E2%80%99s%20Chatroo%20village%2C%20who%20said%20he%20has%20been%20attending%20the%20annual%20festival%20every%20year%20for%20decades%2C%20%E2%80%9CI%20have%20a%20spiritual%20connection%20with%20the%20saint%20and%20I%20have%20been%20blessed%20by%20him%20in%20a%20way%20in%20which%20even