orthway%20about%20her%20experience%20moving%20to%20Norway%20in%202014%20and%20acclimating%20to%20its%20culture.%20The%20conversation%20has%20been%20edited%20for%20length%20and%20clarity.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20family%20moved%20from%20Wisconsin%20to%20Utah%20when%20I%20was%2016%20and%20it%20was%20a%20massive%20culture%20shock.%20As%20hard%20as%20it%20was%2C%20it%20ended%20up%20being%20the%20coolest%20experience%2C%20getting%20out%20of%20a%20small%20town%20of%203%2C000%20people%20and%20into%20Salt%20Lake%20City.%20I%20learned%20that%20the%20world%20is%20so%20big%2C%20and%20there's%20so%20much%20to%20see.%20It%20gave%20me%20a%20wild%20sense%20of%20adventure.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202014%2C%20when%20I%20was%20about%20to%20finish%20college%2C%20I%20figured%20I%20should%20gain%20some%20international%20work%20experience%20and%20it%20would%20give%20me%20a%20competitive%20edge%20in%20the%20US.%20I%20thought%20I%20would%20spend%20two%20years%20abroad%20and%20eventually%20move%20back.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20family%20and%20friends%20were%20very%20supportive.%20My%20parents%20raised%20me%20and%20my%20other%20siblings%20to%20%26quot%3Blove%20them%20and%20leave%20them.%26quot%3B%20I%20bought%20a%20one-way%20ticket%20to%20Oslo%20in%20July%202014%20after%20I%20graduated.%20I%20had%20just%20three%20suitcases.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EI%20wanted%20to%20blend%20in%20as%20a%20Norwegian%2C%20but%20standing%20out%20as%20an%20American%20helped%20me%20at%20work%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThere's%20this%20online%20portal%20called%20FINN.no.%20It's%20a%20marketplace%20like%20Craigslist%2C%20where%20everyone%20does%20all%20of%20their%20looking%20for%20apartment%20rentals.%20I%20found%20a%20very%20small%20place%20outside%20the%20city%20for%20around%20%24500%20per%20month.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20got%20my%20first%20job%20off%20FINN.no%20as%20well.%20It%20was%20for%20a%20woman%20going%20on%20maternity%20leave%2C%20which%20is%20nine%20to%2014%20months%20here.%20I%20got%20my%20foot%20in%20the%20door%20at%20this%20big%20IT%20company%20called%20Visma.%20They%20hired%20me%20for%20a%20year-long%20contract%20as%20a%20content%20marketer.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222787%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Emily%20Northway%20sits%20on%20a%20business%20panel%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64ef7eff0ce10a00183bc63d%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222090%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ENorthway%20said%20Americans%20are%20stereotyped%20abroad%20as%20outgoing%20and%20social.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Emily%20Northway%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThey%20asked%20me%20after%20a%20few%20months%20of%20being%20there%20if%20I%20would%20want%20to%20stay%20on%20permanently%2C%20which%20was%20amazing.%20I%20remember%20I%20started%20crying%20in%20that%20meeting.%20That's%20what%20I%20had%20been%20going%20for.%20That%20was%20my%20ticket%20to%20staying%20in%20Norway.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20I%20first%20moved%20here%2C%20I%20was%20trying%20to%20be%20Norwegian%2C%20but%20then%20I%20started%20using%20my%20Americaness%20to%20my%20benefit%20and%20it%20has%20really%20helped%20me%20at%20every%20job.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENorwegians%20view%20Americans%20as%20being%20very%20outgoing%2C%20outspoken%2C%20and%20social.%20It's%20something%20that%20is%20a%20bit%20exotic%20and%20fun%20for%20them%20because%20it's%20so%20different.%20They're%20generally%20a%20bit%20quieter%20and%20not%20as%20outspoken.%20So%20I%20became%20the%20person%20who%20was%20always%20expected%20to%20be%20social%20and%20outgoing.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20been%20a%20benefit%20for%20me%2C%20but%20it's%20taken%20a%20long%20time%20to%20embrace%20it.%20People%20are%20like%2C%20%26quot%3BYes%2C%20we%20need%20someone%20social%20and%20outgoing%20and%20energetic%20like%20you%20on%20our%20team.%26quot%3B%20Bosses%20like%20having%20a%20representative%20who%20can%20go%20out%20to%20events%20and%20be%20social.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20first%20job%20I%20had%20here%2C%20my%20boss%20told%20me%2C%20%26quot%3BWe%20need%20you%20to%20be%20perfect%20in%20English%20because%20that's%20why%20we%20hired%20you.%26quot%3B%20They%20saw%20previous%20expats%20lose%20some%20of%20their%20English-speaking%20skills%20the%20more%20Norwegian%20they%20learned.%20So%20I%20didn't%20take%20any%20formal%20Norwegian%20classes%20or%20anything%20like%20that.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221034%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Emily%20Northway%20cross-country%20skiing%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64ef802f6f301e00193e5246%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22775%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ENorthway%20planned%20to%20stay%20for%20two%20years%2C%20but%20fell%20in%20love%20with%20Norway%20and%20hasn't%20left.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Emily%20Northway%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EI%20speak%20it%20now.%20I%20hear%20a%20lot%20at%20work%20or%2C%20after%20a%20few%20drinks%2C%20all%20my%20friends%20speak%20Norwegian.%20I'll%20listen%20to%20Norwegian%20podcasts.%20I%20read%20the%20newspapers.%20It's%20been%20a%20slow%20process%20for%20me.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20don't%20plan%20a%20lot.%20I%20just%20kind%20of%20go%20with%20whatever%20feels%20right%20in%20the%20moment.%20I've%20been%20that%20way%20forever.%20And%20I%20think%20what%20has%20kind%20of%20led%20me%20to%20stay.%20I'm%20going%20for%20my%20citizenship%20now%20and%20that%20process%20takes%20like%2022%20months.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20difficult%20for%20me%20to%20say%20where%20I'd%20be%20career%20wise%2C%20had%20I%20stayed%20in%20the%20US.%20It's%20not%20something%20I've%20reflected%20on%20much%2C%20and%20maybe%20that's%20an%20ode%20to%20feeling%20that%20I'm%20right%20where%20I'm%20meant%20to%20be.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20people%20are%20just%20like%20the%20weather%3A%20Cold%20at%20first%2C%20but%20warm%20them%20up%20and%20it's%20magical%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EMaking%20friends%20was%20reall