ce%20them%20to%20sell%20their%20homes%20for%20cut-rate%20prices.%20Concerned%20about%20predatory%20investors%20taking%20advantage%20of%20vulnerable%20families%2C%20Hawaii's%20governor%2C%20Josh%20Green%2C%20called%20for%20a%20moratorium%20on%20damaged-land%20sales%20in%20his%20first%20press%20conference%20after%20the%20fires.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Hawaiian%20fires%20aren't%20the%20first%20time%20investors%20have%20trotted%20out%20this%20playbook%20%E2%80%94%20every%20time%20disaster%20strikes%2C%20the%20%26quot%3Bvultures%26quot%3B%20come%20calling.%20When%20tornadoes%20struck%20Tennessee%20in%202020%2C%20destroying%20771%20businesses%20and%20residences%2C%20the%20Nashville%20Metro%20Council%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.tennessean.com%2Fstory%2Fnews%2Flocal%2F2020%2F03%2F06%2Ftennessee-tornadoes-officials-warn-scammers-predatory-developers%2F4975748002%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epassed%3C%2Fa%3E%20a%20resolution%C2%A0against%20predatory%20developers%20targeting%20residents%20who%20had%20lost%20their%20homes%20and%20offering%20to%20purchase%20plots%20for%20submarket%20rates.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhurricane-ian-estimated-cost-compare-most-expensive-us-storms-ever-2022-10%5C%22%3EHurricane%20Ian%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20struck%20Florida%20last%20fall%2C%20also%20saw%20developers%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.npr.org%2F2022%2F12%2F21%2F1143088346%2Fon-floridas-gulf-coast-developers-eye-properties-ravaged-by-hurricane-ian%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eswarm%20vulnerable%20families%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20hoping%20to%20snap%20up%20destroyed%20properties%20for%20cheap.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EClimate%20disasters%20are%20growing%20more%20common%20and%20more%20destructive%20by%20the%20year.%20And%20after%20the%20initial%20losses%20subside%2C%20the%20profiteers%20inevitably%20arrive.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EStrike%20early%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20vulture%20playbook%20is%20pretty%20straightforward%3A%20Investors%20approach%20affected%20homeowners%20with%20an%20offer%20just%20days%20after%20tragedy%20strikes%2C%20hand%20them%20a%20prewritten%20contract%2C%20and%20try%20to%20reach%20an%20agreement%20on%20the%20spot.%20Once%20acquired%2C%20the%20investors%20turn%20around%20and%20resell%20the%20land%20for%20a%20higher%20price%20%E2%80%94%20sometimes%20without%20ever%20repairing%20the%20property.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22216264%20hurricane%20michael%20damage%20florida%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F5dc9c063695b58064b15e056%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAfter%20Hurricane%20Michael%20struck%20Florida%20in%202018%2C%20home%20sales%20rose%20significantly%2C%20allowing%20disaster%20investors%20to%20reap%20the%20rewards.%3Cp%3EK.C.%20Wilsey%2C%20FEMA%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20strategy%20works%20because%20the%20value%20of%20disaster-struck%20land%20consistently%20bounces%20back%20%E2%80%94%20often%20within%20months%20of%20the%20tragedy.%20A%202021%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.veros.com%2Fhurricanes-and-their-surprising-impact-on-home-prices%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Estudy%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20the%2020%20most-expensive%20hurricanes%20on%20record%20showed%20that%20in%20each%20case%2C%20home%20values%20in%20disaster%20areas%20increased%20at%20a%20higher%20rate%20the%20year%20after%20the%20disaster%20%E2%80%94%20compared%20to%20the%20same%20area%20the%20year%20prior%20and%20the%20national%20average.%20The%20study%20found%20that%20the%20year%20after%20Hurricane%20Katrina%20destroyed%20nearly%20850%2C000%20homes%2C%20home%20values%20in%20New%20Orleans%20increased%20by%2012%25%20compared%20to%20the%20year%20before%20the%20disaster%20%E2%80%94%20and%20the%20gains%20were%209%25%20above%20the%20US%20national%20average%20for%20the%20year.%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nbcmiami.com%2Fnews%2Flocal%2Fhome-sales-up-by-double-digits-in-florida-county-hit-hardest-by-hurricane-michael%2F76184%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EHome%20sales%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20areas%20affected%20by%20Hurricane%20Michael%2C%20which%20struck%20the%20Florida%20panhandle%20in%202018%2C%20killing%2045%20people%20and%20destroying%2060%2C000%20homes%2C%20also%20rose%20significantly%20in%20the%20months%20following%20the%20storm.%20And%20these%20gains%20have%20been%20shown%20to%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dallasfed.org%2F~%2Fmedia%2Fdocuments%2Fresearch%2Fpapers%2F2010%2Fwp1009.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emaintain%20their%20momentum%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20up%20to%20three%20years%20after%20disaster%20strikes.%20A%202019%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wsj.com%2Farticles%2Fthe-new-storm-chasers-real-estate-disaster-investors-11564498767%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EWall%20Street%20Journal%3C%2Fa%3E%20report%20found%20that%20one%20investor%20who%20bought%20up%20properties%20damaged%20by%20Hurricane%20Michael%20was%20able%20to%20earn%20%2410%2C000%20to%20%2415%2C000%20per%20property%20%E2%80%94%20without%20doing%20any%20work%20on%20them.%20Another%20investor%20group%20bought%20up%20more%20than%20600%20properties%20after%20Hurricane%20Katrina%2C%20making%20an%20average%20of%20%2420%2C000%20per%20property%2C%20also%20without%20touching%20most%20of%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPrices%20generally%20go%20up%20post-disaster%20because%20the%20area%20is%20suddenly%20hit%20by%20a%20reduced%20supply%20of%20habitable%20property%2C%20while%20the%20demand%20to%20live%20there%20stays%20the%20same.%20So%20as%20homes%20are%20rebuilt%20or%20the%20debris%20is%20cleared%20for%20a%20new%20structure%2C%20the%20plots%20become%20more%20lucrative.%20The%20rebuilt%20homes%20are%20also%20newer%20than%20the%20ones%20that%20were%20destroyed%2C%20which%20adds%20value.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20venture%20has%20the%20potential%20to%20be%20even%20more%20rewarding%20given%20the%20increasing%20frequency%20of%20natural%20disasters%20in%20the%20US.%20The%20National%20Oceanic%20and%20Atmospheric%20Administration's%20National%20Centers%20for%20Environmental%20Information%20released%20a%20disaster%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.climate.gov%2Fnews-features%2Fblogs%2F2022-us-billion-dollar-weather-and-climate-disasters-historical-context%23%3A~%3Atext%3DAdding%2520the%25202022%2520events%2520to%2C341%2520events%2520exceeds%2520%25242.475%2520trillion.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ereport%3C%2Fa%3E%20last%20year%20that%20found%20the%20US%20suffered%2018%20billion-dollar%20weather%20disasters%20in%202022%2C%20resulting%20in%20%24165%20billion%20in%20total%20damages.%20And%20this%20year%20is%20shaping%20up%20to%20be%20even%20more%20expensive.%20In%20eight%20months%2C%20there%20have%20already%20been%2015%20weather%20disasters%2C%20each%20with%20losses%20exceeding%20%241%20billion.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20disaster%20investors%2C%20these%20increasingly%20common%20tragedies%20are%20an%20opportunity%20to%20win%20big%2C%20and%20the%20residents%20who%20have%20lost%20their%20homes%20pay%20the%20price.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EDesperate%20situations%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20if%20there's%20an%20economic%20explanation%20for%20predatory%20investments%2C%20why%20would%20residents%20sell%20their%20homes%20for%20insultingly%20low%20prices%3F%20One%20obvious%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.journals.uchicago.edu%2Fdoi%2Ffull%2F10.1086%2F705398%23%3A~%3Atext%3DHomeowners%2520flooded%2520out%2520of%2520their%2Cto%2520sell%2520their%2520damaged%2520home.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ereason%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20that%20they%20simply%20don't%20have%20enough%20cash%20on%20hand%20to%20renovate%20their%20property%20back%20to%20a%20habitable%20state.%20For%20most%20families%2C%20their%20homes%20are%20the%20source%20of%20their%20wealth.%20According%20to%20the%20Federal%20Reserve's%20Survey%20of%20Consumer%20Finances%2C%20American%20families%20consistently%20list%20their%20primary%20residence%20as%20their%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Feyeonhousing.org%2F2021%2F02%2Fhomeownership-remains-primary-driver-of-household-wealth%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elargest%20asset%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20with%20home%20ownership%20accounting%20for%2030%25%20of%20household%20wealth%20for%20non-white%20families.%20With%20most%20Americans%20having%20their%20money%20tied%20to%20their%20house%2C%20losing%20it%20to%20a%20wildfire%20or%20other%20natural%20disaster%20can%20be%20devastating.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcost-of-home-insurance-skyrocketing-crushing-homeowners-wildfires-flooding-storms-2023-8%5C%22%3EHome%20insurance%3C%2Fa%3E%20often%20covers%20wildfire%20and%20storm%20damage%2C%20but%20private%20coverage%20is%20increasingly%20more%20costly%20and%20more%20companies%20are%20dropping%20home%20coverage%20altogether%20as%20the%20number%20of%20natural%20disasters%20keep%20rising%2C%20something%20that%20has%20already%20happened%20to%20many%20homeowners%20in%20Florida%20and%20California.%20Those%20left%20with%20no%20insurance%20or%20inadequate%20insurance%20are%20forced%20to%20rely%20on%20tenuous%20government%20aid%20for%20funds%20to%20rebuild.%20But%20federal%20disaster%20relief%20is%20painfully%20slow%20to%20respond%20and%20often%20doesn't%20cover%20most%20of%20the%20costs.%20Individuals%2C%20renters%2C%20and%20homeowners%20are%20all%2C%20in%20theory%2C%20potentially%20eligible%20for%20disaster-relief%20aid.%20However%2C%20qualifying%20for%20aid%20involves%20a%20long%20and%20convoluted%20process.%20Generally%2C%20the%20Federal%20Emergency%20Managment%20Agency%20first%20refers%20homeowners%20to%20the%20Small%20Business%20Administration%20to%20apply%20for%20a%20home-disaster%20loan.%20These%20loans%20require%20applicants%20to%20show%20certain%20levels%20of%20creditworthiness%20and%20an%20ability%20to%20repay%20the%20loan%20with%20interest%2C%20meaning%20many%20lower-%20and%20middle-income%20households%20may%20not%20qualify.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221024%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Hurricane%20Harvey%20FEMA%20aid%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F5a81e170d0307257018b45b6%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22716%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EApplying%20for%20FEMA%20aid%20can%20be%20a%20confusing%20and%20time-consuming%20process.%20And%20the%20average%20payout%20is%20only%20%248%2C000.%3Cp%3EJoe%20Raedle%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3EThe%20next%20option%20is%20to%20apply%20for%20aid%20directly%20from%20FEMA%20%E2%80%94%20a%20process%20that%20requires%20several%20confusing%20and%20time-consuming%20steps.%20First%2C%20a%20presidential%20declaration%20of%20a%20major%20disaster%20is%20required%2C%20then%20residents%20must%20complete%20a%20self-assessment%20and%20application%20for%20relief.%20After%20that%2C%20FEMA%20officials%20conduct%20an%20inspection%20of%20damages%20and%20decide%20how%20much%20relief%20to%20provide.%20This%20process%20can%20take%20up%20to%20a%20month%20%E2%80%94%20and%20for%20other%20expenses%20like%20lodging%20reimbursements%2C%20people%20often%20wait%20up%20to%20two%20months%20for%20the%20funds.%20And%20other%20problems%20often%20arise%3A%20Inconsistent%20damage%20inspections%2C%20minimum%20damage%20amounts%2C%20and%20a%20confusing%20application%20process%20that%20has%20to%20be%20completed%20in%20a%20short%20time%20frame%20often%20leave%20disaster%20victims%20without%20the%20relief%20they%20desperately%20need.%C2%A0%3Cp%3EIn%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.americanbar.org%2Fgroups%2Fcrsj%2Fpublications%2Fhuman_rights_magazine_home%2Fvol--44--no-2--housing%2Fthe-lack-of-proof-of-ownership-in-puerto-rico-is-crippling-repai%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EPuerto%20Rico%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20where%20thousands%20remained%20unhoused%20three%20years%20after%20Hurricane%20Maria%20struck%2C%20or%20in%20tight-knit%20areas%20like%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thenation.com%2Farticle%2Fenvironment%2Flahaina-hawaii-fires-justice%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ELahaina%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Hawaii%2C%20residents%20can%20face%20even%20steeper%20barriers%20to%20aid.%20Both%20Puerto%20Rico%20and%20Lahaina%20have%20a%20history%20of%20informal%20construction%2C%20meaning%20buildings%20often%20lack%20documentation%2C%20and%20homeowners%20can%20have%20a%20hard%20time%20proving%20property%20ownership.%20Given%20FEMA's%20strict%20proof-of-ownership%20requirements%2C%20many%20end%20up%20being%20unqualified%20to%20receive%20FEMA%20relief.%20The%20Urban%20Institute%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.urban.org%2Furban-wire%2Fimproving-disaster-aid-application-process-will-ensure-victims-arent-left-behind%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ereported%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20%26quot%3Bmultigenerational%20family%20homeowners%20without%20active%20mortgages%20or%20who%20live%20in%20rural%20communities%20where%20a%20formal%20title%20is%20not%20readily%20documented%20are%20at%20a%20disadvantage.%26quot%3B%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Government%20Accountability%20Office%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.gao.gov%2Fproducts%2Fgao-20-503%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efound%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20fewer%20than%20half%20of%20the%20applicants%20for%20relief%20under%20FEMA's%20Individual%20and%20Housing%20Assistance%20program%20between%202016%20and%202018%20%E2%80%94%20most%20of%20whom%20were%20uninsured%20or%20had%20an%20income%20under%20%2450%2C000%20%E2%80%94%20qualified%20for%20aid.%20For%20those%20who%20do%20qualify%2C%20the%20FEMA%20funds%20can%20be%20inadequate%20to%20cover%20the%20cost%20of%20rebuilding.%20Payments%20max%20out%20at%20%2436%2C000%20for%20home-rebuilding%20assistance%20and%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theadvocate.com%2Flouisiana_flood_2016%2Fhow-much-money-can-you-expect-from-fema-disaster-grants-sure-to-disappoint-analysis-finds%2Farticle_22c86fe0-64cd-11e6-9bb2-07f95d36ee28.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eaverage%20payout%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20FEMA%20is%20just%20%248%2C000.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20FEMA's%2018-month%20funding%20period%20ends%20%E2%80%94%20assuming%20enough%20money%20has%20been%20approved%20by%20Congress%20%E2%80%94%20a%20last%20backstop%20is%20supposed%20to%20kick%20in%20through%20the%20Department%20of%20Housing%20and%20Urban%20Development's%20Community%20Development%20Block%20Grants.%20The%20grants%20are%20for%20long-term%20rebuilding%20projects%2C%20but%20administration%20of%20the%20funds%20often%20takes%20nearly%20two%20years.%20A%202020%20congressional%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcrsreports.congress.gov%2Fproduct%2Fpdf%2FR%2FR46475%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ereport%3C%2Fa%3E%20found%20that%20New%20York%20still%20had%20more%20than%20%24700%20million%20to%20be%20distributed%20from%20grants%20given%20after%20Hurricane%20Sandy%20in%202017.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20interlocking%20nest%20of%20confusing%20aid%20options%20leaves%20many%20people%20desperate%20and%20willing%20to%20wash%20their%20hands%20of%20the%20properties.%20Some%20families%20may%20look%20at%20the%20damage%20and%20decide%20it's%20better%20for%20them%20to%20sell%20their%20home%20and%20rebuild%20somewhere%20else%20with%20the%20money%20from%20the%20sale.%20But%20other%20families%20may%20feel%20forced%20to%20sell%20their%20home%20for%20less%20than%20it's%20worth%20just%20to%20bridge%20the%20financial%20gap%20between%20the%20destruction%20and%20the%20potential%20aid.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGiven%20the%20threadbare%20relief%20options%2C%20an%20offer%20from%20an%20outside%20investor%20and%20a%20plane%20ticket%20to%20a%20new%20state%20may%20seem%20like%20a%20lifeline.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EHow%20to%20curb%20profiteers%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EInstead%20of%20being%20a%20boon%20for%20residents%20and%20towns%20that%20are%20trying%20to%20build%2C%20outside%20investment%20often%20changes%20the%20character%20of%20an%20area.%20New%20developments%20often%20include%20strip%20malls%20and%20luxury%20hotels%20that%20can%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.yahoo.com%2Fresidents-lahaina-worry-investors-trying-210523021.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ereplace%3C%2Fa%3E%20working-class%20communities%20and%20previously%20affordable%20housing%20%E2%80%94%20usually%20without%20creating%20any%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bloomberg.com%2Fnews%2Farticles%2F2023-07-31%2Fhawaii-s-plan-to-build-more-housing-could-be-national-model%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Enew%20housing%3C%2Fa%3E.%20And%20the%20profits%20that%20out-of-state%20investors%20make%20by%20reselling%20damaged%20properties%20comes%20at%20the%20expense%20of%20the%20struggling%20households%20that%20could%20have%20reaped%20those%20benefits.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20promising%20solution%20is%20a%20piece%20of%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.congress.gov%2Fbill%2F116th-congress%2Fhouse-bill%2F3702%2Ftext%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elegislation%3C%2Fa%3E%20proposed%20in%202019%2C%20the%20Reforming%20Disaster%20Recovery%20Act%2C%20that%20aims%20to%20streamline%20the%20process%20to%20receive%20HUD's%20block%20grants%20so%20that%20communities%20get%20relief%20more%20quickly.%20The%20bill%2C%20which%20passed%20the%20House%20but%20has%20yet%20to%20be%20put%20up%20for%20a%20vote%20in%20the%20Senate%2C%20would%20help%20relieve%20the%20pressure%20on%20homeowners%20to%20sell%20because%20they're%20out%20of%20funds%20to%20rebuild.%20In%20Hawaii%2C%20local%20grassroots%20organizing%20has%20provided%20a%20crucial%20cushion%20for%20people%20who%20lost%20their%20homes.%20Organic%20efforts%20have%20raised%20more%20than%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2FCulturedKanaka%2Fstatus%2F1691895750282850562%3Fs%3D20%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%2412%20million%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20locals%20have%20even%20set%20up%20a%20home-sharing%20system%20where%20people%20have%20volunteered%20to%20host%20families%20who%20have%20lost%20their%20homes.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20while%20moratoriums%20on%20damaged%20land%20sales%20aren't%20a%20long-term%2C%20legally%20tenable%20solution%2C%20there%20are%20ways%20state%20officials%20might%20be%20able%20to%20deter%20disaster%20investors.%20For%20instance%2C%20a%20state%20%26quot%3Bdisaster-relief%20tax%26quot%3B%20could%20be%20applied%20to%20all%20sales%20of%20land%20occurring%20within%20a%20certain%20amount%20of%20time%20after%20a%20presidential%20declaration%20of%20a%20major%20disaster.%20The%20tax%20could%20serve%20as%20an%20indirect%20deterrent%20to%20disaster%20investors%2C%20and%20the%20revenue%20generated%20by%20the%20tax%20could%20be%20redirected%20into%20local%20relief%20efforts%2C%20helping%20other%20families%20who%20intend%20to%20remain%20in%20the%20area.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESince%20the%20climate%20crisis%20isn't%20going%20away%2C%20finding%20a%20solution%20is%20critical.%20As%20the%20threat%20of%20natural%20disasters%20increases%2C%20so%20will%20disaster%20profiteers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fauthor%2Fanthony-dimauro%5C%22%3EAnthony%20DiMauro%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20a%20New%20York-based%20writer.%20His%20work%20has%20appeared%20in%20Bloomberg%2C%20Newsweek%2C%20L.A.%20Review%20of%20Books%20and%20elsewhere.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwho-how-profit-natural-disasters-hurricanes-wildfires-storms-investors-2023-8%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1693476062000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64efb1f90ce10a00183c06c7%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwho-how-profit-natural-disasters-hurricanes-wildfires-storms-investors-2023-8%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Disaster%20investors%20swoop%20in%20after%20hurricanes%2C%20storms%2C%20and%20wildfires%20to%20prey%20on%20vulnerable%20families%20and%20turn%20a%20quick%20profit%20on%20their%20damaged%20homes.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22insider%40insider.com%20(Anthony%20DiMauro)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A21%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwho-how-profit-natural-disasters-hurricanes-wildfires-storms-investors-2023-8%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22SC%20Pulls%20Up%20Gujarat%20HC%20for%20Granting%20Bail%20to%20Murder%20Accused%20Based%20on%20'Personal%20Settlement'%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F25222448%2FSupreme-Court-1.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3EThe%20Supreme%20Court%20has%20pulled%20up%20Gujarat%20high%20court%20for%20granting%20bail%20to%20an%20accused%20in%20a%20murder%20case%20based%20on%20a%20%E2%80%98personal%20settlement%E2%80%99%20between%20the%20accused%20and%20the%20son%20of%20the%20deceased.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20quashing%20the%20high%20court%E2%80%99s%20order%20and%20ordering%20the%20accused%20to%20surrender%20immediately%20before%20the%20trial%20court%2C%20it%20also%20admonished%20the%20Gujarat%20government%20for%20not%20challenging%20the%20bail%20order.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CStrangely%20enough%20one%20of%20the%20considerations%20that%20has%20weighed%20with%20the%20learned%20Single%20Judge%20includes%20the%20fact%20that%20the%20respondent%20No.%202%20%5Bthe%20accused%5D%20has%20filed%20a%20settlement%20arrived%20at%20with%20the%20original%20complainant%20%5Bson%20of%20the%20deceased%5D%20and%20the%20affidavit%20of%20the%20original%20complainant%20confirmed%20the%20said%20settlement%2C%20that%20too%20in%20respect%20of%20an%20offence%20under%20Section%20302%20%5Bpunishment%20for%20murder%5D%20of%20the%20IPC%20%5BIndian%20Penal%20Code%5D%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20apex%20court%20said%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.livelaw.in%2Fsupreme-court%2Fsupreme-court-surprised-by-gujarat-hc-granting-bail-to-murder-accused-based-on-settlement-with-victims-son-chastises-state-for-not-challenging-order-236632%5C%22%3Eaccording%20to%20%3Cem%3ELivelaw%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20issue%20reached%20the%20division%20bench%20of%20Justice%20Hima%20Kohli%20and%20Justice%20Rajesh%20Bindal%20at%20the%20top%20court%20when%20one%20of%20the%20injured%20persons%20in%20the%20crime%20appealed%20against%20the%20high%20court%E2%80%99s%20bail%20order.%20The%20accused%20attacked%20Parvinbahi%20(the%20deceased)%20and%20the%20appellant%20on%20September%2017%2C%202021.%20While%20the%20appellant%20sustained%20injuries%2C%20Parvinbhai%20succumbed.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20top%20court%20also%20objected%20to%20the%20high%20court%E2%80%99s%20observations%20made%20in%20the%20bail%20order%20that%20there%20are%20no%20criminal%20antecedents%20on%20the%20part%20of%20the%20accused%2C%20pointing%20out%20that%20the%20accused%20was%20arrested%20after%20being%20released%20on%20bail%20in%20connection%20with%20another%20first%20information%20report%20(FIR).%20While%20noting%20that%20the%20accused%20had%20spent%20%E2%80%9Cmerely%E2%80%9D%20six%20months%20in%20jail%20from%20September%2023%2C%202021%20to%20February%2018%2C%202022%2C%20the%20apex%20court%20said%20there%20is%20a%20propensity%20on%20the%20part%20of%20the%20accused%20towards%20criminal%20behaviour%20and%20must%2C%