th-session-of-united-nations-general-assembly-in-new-york%2Farticle36668955.ece%5C%22%3EUnited%20Nations%20General%20Assembly%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20September%202021%20and%20at%20the%20global%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thehindu.com%2Fnews%2Fnational%2Findia-mother-of-democracy-home-to-idea-of-elected-leaders-much-before-rest-of-world-pm-modi%2Farticle66675267.ece%23%3A~%3Atext%3DModi%2520said%2520at%2520the%2520plenary%2CModi%2520said.%5C%22%3ESummit%20for%20Democracy%3C%2Fa%3E%20held%20in%20March%20this%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20Modi%20government%20wants%20to%20go%20to%20the%20town%20highlighting%20India%E2%80%99s%20democratic%20traditions%2C%20the%20reality%2C%20however%2C%20has%20been%20India%E2%80%99s%20consistently%20poor%20showing%20on%20global%20indices%20measuring%20democracy.%20In%20March%20this%20year%2C%20Sweden-based%20V-Dem%20(Varieties%20of%20Democracy)%20Institute%20described%20India%20as%20%E2%80%9C%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Findia-autocratiser-v-dem-report-2023%5C%22%3Eone%20of%20the%20worst%20autocratisers%20in%20the%20last%2010%20years%3C%2Fa%3E%E2%80%9C%2C%20ranking%20it%20at%20the%2097th%20place%20on%20the%20Liberal%20Democracy%20Index%20among%20the%20bottom%2040-50%25%20of%20countries.%20Even%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Feconomictimes.indiatimes.com%2Fnews%2Fpolitics-and-nation%2Findia-falls-to-53rd-position-in-eius-democracy-index-dubbed-as-flawed-democracy%2Farticleshow%2F80665859.cms%3Ffrom%3Dmdr%5C%22%3EEconomist%20Intelligence%20Unit%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20the%20US%20think%20tank%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ffreedomhouse.org%2Fcountry%2Findia%2Ffreedom-world%2F2023%5C%22%3EFreedom%20House%3C%2Fa%3E%20have%20rated%20India%20poorly%20on%20democracy.%20All%20of%20them%20have%20pointed%20to%20the%20curtailment%20of%20rights%20and%20freedom%20of%20speech%20in%20the%20last%20nine%20years%20of%20the%20Modi%20government.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20stark%20contrast%20to%20the%20existing%20reality%20on%20the%20ground%2C%20the%20%E2%80%98Mother%20of%20Democracy%E2%80%99%20exhibition%20will%20project%20India%20as%20a%20shining%20example%20of%20liberal%20democracy.%20It%20will%20capture%20the%20journey%20of%20Indian%20democratic%20traditions%20from%20the%20Vedic%20times%2C%20and%20the%20references%20made%20in%20the%20Vedas%20to%20political%20power%20being%20exercised%20by%20broad-based%20consultative%20bodies.%20The%20exhibition%20also%20aims%20to%20touch%20upon%20several%20historical%20references%20to%20republic%20states%20in%20ancient%20India%2C%20where%20the%20rulers%20were%20not%20hereditary.%20Besides%20these%2C%20the%20exhibition%20will%20also%20showcase%20present-day%20India%E2%80%99s%20governance%20tools%2C%20which%20are%20said%20to%20be%20democratising%20service%20delivery%2C%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Tribune%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.tribuneindia.com%2Fnews%2Findia%2Fmother-of-democracy-exhibition-to-greet-leaders-at-delhi-summit-venue-539804%5C%22%3Ereported%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20the%20principal%20secretary%20to%20the%20prime%20minister%2C%20P.K.%20Mishra%2C%20held%20the%20ninth%20review%20meeting%20of%20the%20G20%20Coordination%20Committee%20on%20Wednesday%2C%20August%2030.%20He%20took%20stock%20of%20arrangements%20for%20the%20G20%20New%20Delhi%20Leaders%E2%80%99%20Summit%2C%20including%20logistical%2C%20protocol%2C%20security%2C%20and%20media-related%20arrangements.%20The%20meeting%20was%20attended%20by%20senior%20officers%20from%20the%20G20%20secretariat%20and%20ministries%20of%20external%20affairs%2C%20home%2C%20culture%2C%20information%20and%20broadcasting%2C%20and%20telecom%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpib.gov.in%2FPressReleaseIframePage.aspx%3FPRID%3D1953513%5C%22%3Eaccording%20to%20a%20release%20from%20Press%20Information%20Bureau%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EItems%20from%20installations%20to%20give%20a%20facelift%20to%20Delhi%20ahead%20of%20summit%20stolen%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20administration%E2%80%99s%20attempts%20to%20give%20a%20facelift%20to%20the%20national%20capital%20ahead%20of%20the%20summit%20are%20running%20into%20trouble%20with%20many%20items%20used%20in%20various%20installations%20in%20and%20around%20the%20city%20being%20stolen.%20High-end%20lights%2C%20copper%20wires%2C%20and%20even%20cheap%20minor%20fittings%20like%20nozzles%20have%20been%20stolen%20from%20these%20installations%2C%20%3Cem%3EHindustan%20Times%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.hindustantimes.com%2Fcities%2Fdelhi-news%2Fthieves-target-new-delhi-installations-ahead-of-g20-summit-stealing-lights-copper-wires-and-rubber-nozzles-officials-101693416731450.html%5C%22%3Equoted%3C%2Fa%3E%20officials%20from%20the%20public%20works%20department%20as%20saying.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThey%20said%20so%20far%2050%20complaints%20have%20been%20filed%20with%20the%20police%2C%20but%20to%20no%20avail%2C%20as%20fresh%20incidents%20of%20thefts%20are%20being%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20last%20five%20months%2C%20the%20administration%20has%20put%20up%C2%A030%20fountains%20in%20various%20parts%20of%20the%20Capital%2C%20including%20at%20Delhi%20Gate%2C%20around%20India%20Gate%2C%20near%20Rajghat%20as%20well%20as%20on%20the%20Dhaula%20Kuan%20stretch.%20An%20expensive%20sensor%20unit%20for%20a%20fountain%20installed%20near%20Pragati%20Maidan%2C%20costing%20Rs%202.5%20lakh%2C%20has%20gone%20missing%2C%20officials%20said%2C%20adding%20that%20thieves%20have%20even%20not%20spared%20minor%20fittings%20and%20nozzles%20which%20cost%20less%20than%20Rs%20500.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CSuch%20incidents%20are%20not%20ending.%20In%20some%20cases%2C%20multiple%20thefts%20have%20occurred%20at%20the%20same%20site%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20newspaper%20quoted%20a%20PWD%20official%20as%20saying.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20addition%20to%20their%20usual%20duties%2C%C2%A0PWD%20field%20workers%20and%20police%20personnel%20have%20now%20been%20instructed%20to%20keep%20a%20close%20tab%20on%20new%20installations%20over%20the%20next%2010%20days.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1693463436000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F31111612%2FF2iRa-FWUAEidc_.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fmother-of-democracy-special-exhibition-to-greet-world-leaders-at-g20-summit-in-delhi%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22While%20the%20Narendra%20Modi%20government%20wants%20to%20go%20to%20the%20town%20highlighting%20India's%20democratic%20traditions%2C%20the%20reality%2C%20however%2C%20has%20been%20India's%20consistently%20poor%20showing%20on%20global%20indices%20measuring%20democracy.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A2%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fmother-of-democracy-special-exhibition-to-greet-world-leaders-at-g20-summit-in-delhi%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22How%20the%20Constitution%20Is%20Being%20Used%20to%20Advance%20the%20Hindu%20State%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F05%2F20123532%2FIMG_2186.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20cursory%20glance%20at%20recent%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theguardian.com%2Fworld%2F2020%2Ffeb%2F20%2Fhindu-supremacists-nationalism-tearing-india-apart-modi-bjp-rss-jnu-attacks%5C%22%3Enews%20reports%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0suggests%20India%20is%20a%20very%20different%20place%20today%20than%20it%20was%20a%20decade%20ago.%20There%20is%20rampant%20and%20extreme%20violence%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theguardian.com%2Fworld%2F2023%2Faug%2F04%2Fhow-will-any-muslim-feel-safe-spate-of-attacks-increases-tensions-in-india%23%3A~%3Atext%3DIndia%2520has%2520suffered%2520a%2520spate%2520of%2520anti%252DMuslim%2520attacks%26amp%3Btext%3D%25E2%2580%259CSince%2520this%2520government%2520came%2520into%2Cwhat%2527s%2520happening%2520to%2520our%2520society.%5C%22%3Eagainst%20those%20who%20identify%20as%20Muslim%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20dissenters%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Findia-modi-anti-national-protest-arrest-sedition-authoritarianism%5C%22%3E%C2%A0irrespective%20of%20their%20religion%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20or%20who%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findianexpress.com%2Farticle%2Findia%2Fchennai-seven-movie-goers-booked-for-disrespecting-the-national-anthem-4422897%2F%5C%22%3Edo%20not%20sing%20the%20national%20anthem%C2%A0%3C%2Fa%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.india.com%2Fnews%2Findia%2Fdelhi-violence-man-brutally-beaten-forced-to-sing-national-anthem-amid-riots-dies-3957294%2F%5C%22%3Ein%20public%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EVigilantes%20inflict%20violence%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Facleddata.com%2F2021%2F05%2F03%2Fcow-protection-legislation-and-vigilante-violence-in-india%2F%5C%22%3Ein%20the%20name%20of%20protecting%20the%20cow.%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0Student%20and%20faculty%20are%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fsix-tables-that-tell-the-story-of-academic-unfreedom-in-india%5C%22%3E%C2%A0arrested%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0for%20opinions%20and%20scholarship%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.telegraphindia.com%2Findia%2Fcentral-university-of-kerala-bans-anti-national-lectures%2Fcid%2F1829916%5C%22%3Edeemed%20%E2%80%98anti-national%E2%80%99%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Statements%20made%20on%20social%20media%20that%20criticise%20the%20government%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thehindu.com%2Fnews%2Fnational%2Fother-states%2Fjk-sacks-3-employees-including-engineer-and-teacher-for-anti-national-activities%2Farticle66557130.ece%5C%22%3Elead%20to%20dismissal%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.indiatoday.in%2Findia%2Fstory%2Funacademy-what-led-to-controversy-video-karan-sangwan-roman-saini-2423005-2023-08-18%5C%22%3Efrom%20the%20workplace%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Permits%20for%20overseas%20funds%20for%20NGOs%20are%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.devex.com%2Fnews%2Fin-india-ngos-face-funding-bans-reel-under-strangulating-laws-102404%5C%22%3Etaken%20away%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20think%20tanks%20become%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.outlookindia.com%2Fnational%2Fraids-at-think-tank-cpr-global-ngo-oxfam-and-media-foundation-ipsmf-in-alleged-fcra-case-news-221767%5C%22%3Etargets%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0of%20investigative%20agencies%2C%20and%20passports%20are%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.trust.org%2Fitem%2F20210827102129-acg5f%5C%22%3Ewithheld%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20may%20sound%20like%20a%20textbook%20authoritarian%20theocracy%2C%20in%20which%20the%20rule%20of%20law%2C%20democracy%20and%20secularism%20have%20been%20swept%20aside.%20Or%20%E2%80%93%20given%20the%20prevalence%20of%20street%20violence%20and%20state-sanctioned%20vigilantism%20%E2%80%93%20perhaps%20a%20more%20precise%20label%20would%20be%C2%A0%3Ci%3Epopulist%C2%A0%3C%2Fi%3Eauthoritarian%20theocracy.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIf%20this%20were%20the%20case%2C%20then%20the%20Indian%20story%20would%20be%20similar%20to%20the%20rise%20of%20authoritarian%20governments%20across%20the%20world.%20In%20India%2C%20however%2C%20these%20developments%20have%20not%20been%20brought%20about%20by%20an%20erosion%20of%20formal%20legal%20institutions%20and%20a%20disregard%20for%20the%20Constitution%2C%20but%20rather%20in%20many%20ways%20facilitated%20by%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndia%E2%80%99s%20identity%20has%20been%20shaped%20by%20ethno-religious%20nationalism%20and%20aided%20by%20%E2%80%98constitutional%20accommodation%E2%80%99%20%E2%80%93%20the%20inclusion%20of%20elements%20in%20the%20text%20which%20can%20be%20mobilised%20to%20create%20division.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnimating%20ethno-religious%20nationalism%20within%20the%20scope%20of%20the%20Indian%20Constitution%20is%20what%20has%20led%20to%20the%20erosion%20of%20democratic%20values.%20A%20key%20component%20in%20this%20process%20can%20be%20found%20in%20the%20policy%20of%20Indian%20citizenship.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20some%20leading%20constitutional%20law%20scholars%20hold%20that%20the%20Indian%20constitution%20is%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpapers.ssrn.com%2Fsol3%2Fpapers.cfm%3Fabstract_id%3D3367266%5C%22%3Edying%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20it%20is%20very%20much%20alive%20%E2%80%93%20but%20it%20has%20been%20appropriated%20for%20political%20ends%2C%20in%20part%20through%20constitutional%20accommodation.%20This%20accommodation%20of%20ethno-religious%20nationalist%20elements%20offers%20legitimacy%20to%20the%20politics%20of%20the%20current%20government%20and%20allows%20for%20the%20construction%20of%20a%20Hindu%20state%20that%20can%20exist%20in%20perpetuity.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EThe%20question%20of%20citizenship%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETwo%20primary%20elements%20have%20facilitated%20this%20situation.%20The%20first%20is%20a%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.constitutionofindia.net%2Farticles%2Farticle-11-parliament-to-regulate-the-right-of-citizenship-by-law%2F%5C%22%3E%E2%80%98notwithstanding%E2%80%99%20clause%20on%20citizenship%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0inserted%20into%20the%20constitution%20to%20allow%20the%20legislature%20to%20deal%20with%20thorny%20questions%20of%20citizenship%20at%20the%20time%20of%20the%20Partition%20of%20India%20in%201947.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20discussions%20in%20the%20Constituent%20Assembly%20Debates%20(CAD)%20were%20ongoing%2C%20the%20Indian%20Independence%20Act%201947%20resulted%20in%20the%20dissolution%20of%20the%20British%20empire%20and%20divided%20the%20Union%20into%20two%20separate%20dominions%20%E2%80%93%20India%20and%20Pakistan%2C%20separated%20by%20the%20Radcliffe%20Line.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPartition%20was%20characterised%20by%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.com%2Fnews%2Fuk-scotland-40874496%5C%22%3Eraging%20communal%20violence%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20death%20toll%20was%20more%20than%20a%20million%20people.%20There%20were%20countless%20rapes%2C%20loss%20of%20property%2C%20mutilation%20and%20disease.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAfter%20Partition%2C%20the%20tone%20and%20substance%20of%20the%20CAD%20changed.%20One%20area%20where%20this%20change%20was%20noticeable%20was%20on%20the%20question%20of%20citizenship.%20Prior%20to%20Partition%2C%20citizenship%20was%20accepted%20on%C2%A0%3Ci%3Ejus%20soli%3C%2Fi%3E%C2%A0(citizenship%20by%20birth)%20terms%2C%20but%20the%20discussion%20increasingly%20featured%20an%20ethnicity-based%20idea%20of%C2%A0%3Ci%3Ejus%20sanguinis%3C%2Fi%3E%C2%A0citizenship%2C%20where%20one%20has%20to%20prove%20lineage.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20text%20adopted%20included%20a%20citizenship%20by%20birth%20clause%20and%20some%20Partition-specific%20clauses%2C%20there%20was%20also%20an%20inclusion%20of%20a%20%E2%80%98notwithstanding%E2%80%99%20clause%20in%20Article%2011%20of%20the%20Constitution%20that%20deferred%20questions%20of%20citizenship%20to%20be%20settled%20by%20ordinary%20law.%20This%20meant%20that%20Indian%20citizenship%20effectively%20became%20a%20legislative%20rather%20than%20constitutional%20question.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20one%20scholar%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpapers.ssrn.com%2Fsol3%2Fpapers.cfm%3Fabstract_id%3D3565551%5C%22%3Eputs%20it%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20%E2%80%9CWhat%20does%20the%20Constitution%20say%20about%20citizenship%3F%20The%20answer%3A%20nothing%E2%80%9D.%20The%20absence%20of%20constitutional%20safeguards%20allowed%20for%20the%20Citizenship%20Amendment%20Act%2C%20National%20Register%20of%20Citizens%2C%20and%20citizens%20who%20needed%20to%20prove%20themselves.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESuch%20deferral%20could%20be%20explained%20by%20the%20belief%20of%20the%20liberal%20drafters%20of%20the%20Constitution%20such%20as%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.constitutionofindia.net%2Fmembers%2Fb-r-ambedkar%2F%5C%22%3EBhimrao%20Ambedkar%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0that%20the%20Partition%20was%20provisional%20(the%20provisions%20on%20citizenship%20were%20decided%20%E2%80%98%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.constitutionofindia.net%2Fdebates%2F10-aug-1949%2F%5C%22%3Ead%20hoc%20for%20the%20time%20being%3C%2Fa%3E%E2%80%98)%2C%20or%20there%20was%20simply%20too%20much%20faith%20in%20subsequent%20governments%20by%20the%20Indian%20National%20Congress.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThus%2C%20the%20process%20of%20reaching%20a%20consensus%20while%20placating%20ethno-religious%20nationalists%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fonlinelibrary.wiley.com%2Fdoi%2Fabs%2F10.1111%2Fj.1469-8129.2010.00435.x%5C%22%3Erequired%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0%E2%80%98avoidance%20of%20clear%20decisions%E2%80%99%2C%20and%20using%20%E2%80%98ambivalent%2C%20vague%20legal%20language%E2%80%99.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%201971%2C%20with%20the%20secession%20of%20East%20Pakistan%20from%20Pakistan%20and%20the%20formation%20of%20Bangladesh%2C%20new%20fears%20were%20politically%20inflamed%20in%20the%20state%20of%20Assam%20on%20the%20dilution%20of%20an%20ethnic%20and%20linguistic%20majority.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EDoubtful%20voters%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20solution%20was%20the%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nrcassam.nic.in%2Fwha_nrc.html%5C%22%3ENational%20Register%20of%20Citizens%20(NRC)%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20the%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatelessnessandcitizenshipreview.com%2Findex.php%2Fjournal%2Farticle%2Fview%2F141%2F67%5C%22%3Einterpretation%20given%20by%20courts%C2%A0%3C%2Fa%3Edrawing%20on%20the%20Foreigners%20Act%201946%20where%20citizens%20needed%20to%20prove%20themselves%2C%20creating%20the%20category%20of%20the%20%E2%80%98%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fassam-doubtful-voters-citizenship-nrc%5C%22%3Edoubtful%20voter%3C%2Fa%3E%E2%80%98.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20deferral%20of%20citizenship%20to%20ordinary%20law%20without%20constitutional%20guidance%20allowed%20for%20the%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findiancitizenshiponline.nic.in%2FUserGuide%2FE-gazette_2019_20122019.pdf%5C%22%3ECitizenship%20Amendment%20Act%20(CAA)%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20CAA%2C%20passed%20by%20Parliament%20in%20December%202019%2C%20means%20that%20%E2%80%98illegal%20migrants%E2%80%99%20of%20Hindu%2C%20Sikh%2C%20Jain%2C%20Buddhist%2C%20Parsi%20or%20Christian%20faith%20from%20Afghanistan%2C%20Pakistan%20or%20Bangladesh%20who%20escaped%20persecution%20and%20arrived%20in%20India%20before%202014%20can%20be%20fast-tracked%20to%20citizenship.%20But%20not%20if%20they%20are%20Muslim.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThus%2C%20the%20notwithstanding%20clause%20that%20was%20constitutionally%20accommodated%20allowed%20for%20two%20key%20legislative%20acts%20on%20citizenship%3A%20the%20NRC%20and%20revival%20of%20colonial%20legislation%20on%20the%20foreigner%20who%20needs%20to%20prove%20their%20citizenship%2C%20and%20the%20CAA%20that%20allows%20for%20privileged%20access%20of%20Hindus.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20addition%20to%20citizenship%2C%20the%20other%20significant%20instance%20of%20constitutional%20accommodation%20is%20the%20textual%20presence%20of%20ethno-religious%20nationalism%20through%20the%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Funveiling-indias-long-history-of-hypocrisy-on-cow-slaughter-laws%5C%22%3Eprohibition%20against%20cow%20slaughter%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0in%20the%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpapers.ssrn.com%2Fsol3%2Fpapers.cfm%3Fabstract_id%3D2411046%5C%22%3EDirective%20Principles%20of%20State%20Policy%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20provision%20was%20lobbied%20for%20by%20the%20All-India%20Hindu%20Mahasabha%20and%20supported%20by%20the%20heavily%20funded%20Anti-Cow%20Slaughter%20League%20during%20the%20drafting%20of%20the%20Constitution.%20Unlike%20fundamental%20rights%2C%20the%20Directive%20Principles%20are%20unenforceable%20in%20courts.%20However%2C%20as%20the%20Constitution%20requires%20states%20to%20have%20regard%20to%20these%20principles%20in%20law-making%2C%20they%20have%20the%20potential%20to%20acquire%20potency%20during%20elections.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20provision%20against%20cow%20slaughter%20was%20interpreted%20as%20a%20beef%20ban%2C%20and%20states%20such%20as%20Haryana%2C%20Maharashtra%20and%20Uttar%20Pradesh%20experienced%20mass%20agitation.%20One%20scholar%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.tandfonline.com%2Fdoi%2Fabs%2F10.1080%2F00856401.2017.1352646%3FjournalCode%3Dcsas20%5C%22%3Eobserves%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0that%20%E2%80%9Cembedding%20cow%20protection%20in%20the%20Constitution%20represented%20the%20first%20substantial%20victory%20of%20the%20nascent%20Hindu%20right%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20prevalence%20of%20the%20Partition%2C%20the%20seepage%20of%20colonial%20legislation%20into%20ordinary%20law%20via%20a%20notwithstanding%20clause%20on%20citizenship%20and%20the%20potency%20of%20the%20Directive%20Principles%20are%20all%20but%20ignored%20in%20current%20leading%20accounts%20of%20Indian%20constitutionalism.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESuch%20accounts%20present%20a%20benign%20view%20of%20the%20past%20when%20the%20Constitution%20was%20drafted%2C%20which%20has%20been%20diluted%20in%20an%20aberrant%20violent%20present.%20In%20contrast%2C%20these%20factors%20created%20a%20context%20for%20the%20CAA%20and%20NRC%20to%20be%20put%20in%20place%2C%20along%20with%20its%20attendant%20discourse%20on%20citizens%20and%20non-citizen%20others.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20constitutional%20accommodation%20and%20mobilisation%20of%20communal%20nationalism%20in%20constructing%20a%20Hindu%20state%20challenges%20the%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpress.princeton.edu%2Fbooks%2Fhardcover%2F9780691649917%2Findia-as-a-secular-state%5C%22%3Ereceived%20wisdom%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0that%20India%E2%80%99s%20secular%20constitution%20can%20be%20contrasted%20against%20Pakistan%E2%80%99s%20religious%20constitution.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findiankanoon.org%2Fdoc%2F37494799%2F%5C%22%3EEven%20the%20Supreme%20Court%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0has%20interpreted%20secularism%20as%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fread.dukeupress.edu%2Fsouth-atlantic-quarterly%2Farticle-abstract%2F113%2F1%2F109%2F3721%2FA-Leap-of-Faith-The-Construction-of-Hindu%3FredirectedFrom%3Dfulltext%5C%22%3Erooted%20in%20Hindu%20scriptures%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0that%20exemplify%20an%20Indic%20way%20of%20life.%20This%20explains%20why%20there%20is%20state%20interference%20with%20school%20curricula%2C%20such%20as%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Feducation%2Fh-for-hindu-rashtra-is-a-rationalised-periodic-table-of-elements-in-the-making%5C%22%3Eremoval%20of%20content%20on%20the%20Partition%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Rather%20than%20denying%20history%2C%20in%20India%20there%20is%20the%20rewriting%20and%20glorification%20of%20an%20Indic%20history%2C%20a%20history%20of%20the%20Hindu%20state.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3EDr%20Suryapratim%20Roy%3C%2Fi%3E%3Ci%3E%C2%A0is%20Assistant%20Professor%2C%20School%20of%20Law%2C%20Trinity%20College%20Dublin.%20He%20leads%20a%20seminar%20on%20Emergency%20Law%2C%20and%20writes%20on%20climate%20law%2C%20citizenship%2C%20and%20Indian%20constitutionalism.%20%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3EDr%20Rahul%20Sambaraju%20is%20a%20Lecturer%20in%20Qualitative%20Social%20Psychology%20at%20The%20University%20of%20Edinburgh%2C%20UK.%20He%20uses%20discursive%20methods%20to%20examine%20nationalism%2C%20%C2%A0race%20and%20racism%2C%20and%20migration%20and%20refuge-seeking.%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3Ci%3EOriginally%20published%20under%C2%A0%3C%2Fi%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcreativecommons.org%2Flicenses%2Fby%2F4.0%2F%5C%22%3E%3Ci%3ECreative%20Commons%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Ci%3E%C2%A0by%C2%A0%3C%2Fi%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2F360info.org%2F%5C%22%3E%3Ci%3E360info%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Ci%3E%E2%84%A2.%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1693462830000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F05%2F20123532%2FIMG_2186.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fcommunalism%2Fconstitution-hindu-rashtra-advance%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22While%20some%20leading%20constitutional%20law%20scholars%20hold%20that%20the%20Indian