03%2F10095529%2FVladimir_Putin_and_Xi_Jinping_2019-06-05_63.jpeg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Close%20on%20the%20heels%20of%20speculation%20that%20Chinese%20president%20Xi%20Jinping%20may%20be%20giving%20the%20G20%20meet%20hosted%20by%20New%20Delhi%20a%20miss%2C%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E%20has%20learnt%20from%20sources%20that%20it%20is%20Chinese%20premiere%20Li%20Qiang%20who%20will%20attend%20the%20event.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndian%20authorities%2C%20the%20sources%20said%2C%20had%20known%20for%20a%20month%20that%20Xi%20will%20give%20the%20leaders%E2%80%99%20summit%20a%20miss.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20will%20be%20Li%E2%80%99s%20first%20visit%20to%20India%20as%20premier.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20G20%20summit%20will%20be%20held%20in%20New%20Delhi%20from%20September%208%20to%2010.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EXi%20had%20last%20visited%20India%20in%202019%20for%20the%20second%20edition%20of%20the%20informal%20summit%20at%20Mamallapuram.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESince%20he%20took%20over%20leadership%2C%20Xi%20Jinping%20has%20attended%20all%20the%20in-person%20G20%20summit%20meetings%20from%202013%20to%202019.%20After%20the%20break%20for%20COVID-19%2C%20the%20next%20physical%20summit%20meeting%20took%20place%20in%20Rome%20in%202021.%20At%20that%20time%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.co.uk%2Fnews%2Fworld-asia-china-58929296%23%3A~%3Atext%3DIn%2520September%252C%2520Chinese%2520officials%2520told%2520Italian%2520diplomats%2520that%2CThey%2520cited%2520China%2527s%2520Covid%2520regulations%2520as%2520the%2520reason%5C%22%3EBeijing%20had%20said%20that%20Xi%E2%80%99s%20absence%3C%2Fa%3E%20was%20due%20to%20China%E2%80%99s%20own%20regulations%20on%20COVID%2C%20which%20had%20been%20highly%20restrictive.%20The%20effects%20of%20the%20pandemic%20were%20still%20lingering%20in%20many%20places%20of%20the%20world%20then.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20has%20been%20no%20response%20from%20the%20Indian%20government%20on%20the%20matter%20yet.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EXi%20and%20Indian%20prime%20minister%20Narendra%20Modi%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fdiplomacy%2Fmodi-raised-border-stand-off-issue-in-conversation-with-xi-at-brics-says-foreign-secretary%5C%22%3Emet%20earlier%20this%20month%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20what%20was%20their%20first%20direct%20%E2%80%98conversation%E2%80%99%20in%20over%20nine%20months%2C%20on%20the%20sidelines%20of%20the%20BRICS%20Summit%20in%20South%20Africa.%20China%20later%20publicly%20claimed%20that%20the%20informal%20talks%20were%20based%20on%20an%20Indian%20request.%20India%20responded%2C%20based%20on%20sources%2C%20that%20there%20was%20a%20%E2%80%9Cpending%20request%E2%80%9D%20from%20China%20for%20a%20meeting.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWith%20Chinese%20President%20Xi%20not%20attending%2C%20it%20would%20mean%20that%20two%20heads%20of%20states%20would%20not%20be%20attending%20the%20G-20%20summit%20as%20Russian%20President%20Putin%20is%20also%20not%20attending%20the%20meeting.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EChina%20and%20India%20are%20currently%20embroiled%20in%20a%20three-year-old%20military%20stand-off%20at%20the%20Line%20of%20Actual%20Control%20in%20eastern%20Ladakh%20since%20April-May%202020.%20India%20had%20largely%20frozen%20ties%20especially%20after%20a%20clash%20in%20June%202020%20which%20led%20to%20the%20death%20of%2020%20Indian%20soldiers%20and%20at%20least%20four%20Chinese%20soldiers.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFollowing%20the%20%E2%80%98conversation%E2%80%99%20in%20Johannesburg%2C%20Chinese%20ministry%20of%20natural%20resources%20released%20the%202023%20edition%20of%20the%20standard%20map%20of%20China%20which%20continued%20to%20show%20Arunachal%20Pradesh%20and%20Aksai%20Chin%20within%20its%20boundary.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20this%20was%20a%20routine%20exercise%2C%20the%20timing%20of%20the%20release%20and%20the%20publicity%20given%20to%20it%20through%20a%20state-run%20English%20tabloid%20raised%20eyebrows%20in%20New%20Delhi.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20riled%20up%20the%20Indian%20opposition%20and%20led%20to%20the%20Ministry%20of%20External%20Affairs%20to%20lodge%20a%20%E2%80%9Cstrong%20protest%E2%80%9D.%20China%20responded%20that%20it%20was%20a%20%E2%80%9Croutine%20exercise%20of%20sovereignty%E2%80%9D%20and%20urged%20India%20to%20%E2%80%9Cnot%20over-interpret%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1693459932000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F03%2F10095529%2FVladimir_Putin_and_Xi_Jinping_2019-06-05_63.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fdiplomacy%2Fxi-jinping-g20-li-qiang%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22This%20will%20be%20Li's%20first%20visit%20to%20India%20as%20premier.%C2%A0%C2%A0%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A2%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fdiplomacy%2Fxi-jinping-g20-li-qiang%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22The%20Rhetoric%20of%20Akhand%20Bharat%20and%20India%E2%80%99s%20Civilisational%20Claims%20in%20South%20Asia%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F06%2F02234414%2FUntitled-design-2023-06-02T234320.741.png%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EA%20mural%20in%20India%E2%80%99s%20new%20parliament%20building%20has%20become%20an%20object%20of%20controversy%20in%20South%20Asia.%20Alluding%20to%20the%20idea%20of%C2%A0%3Ci%3EAkhand%20Bharat%3C%2Fi%3E%2C%20this%20ancient%20map%20appears%20to%20depict%20most%20of%20the%20current%20South%20Asian%20states%20as%20part%20of%20a%20larger%2C%20undivided%20polity%20of%20the%20past.%20Subsequently%2C%20the%20reveal%20has%20evoked%20negative%20responses%20from%20Pakistan%2C%20Nepal%2C%20and%20Bangladesh.%20These%20states%20raised%20concerns%20about%20how%20the%20claims%20implied%20in%20the%20map%20threaten%20their%20independence%20and%20sovereignty.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHistorically%2C%20a%20number%20of%20nation-states%20have%20turned%20to%20civilisational%20arguments%20to%20couch%20their%20political%20claims%2C%20drawing%20from%20a%20cultural%20invocation%20of%20the%20past%20to%20legitimise%20the%20political%20claims%20of%20the%20present.%20For%20instance%2C%20consider%20the%20relationship%20between%20civilisational%20aspirations%20and%20irredentism%2C%20i.e.%20claims%20on%20other%20nations%E2%80%99%20territories%20on%20an%20ethnic%20or%20historical%20basis.%20States%20assert%20territorial%20claims%20borrowing%20from%20a%20civilisational%20understanding%20of%20what%20its%20contours%20were%20in%20the%20past.%20Is%20India%E2%80%99s%20South%20Asia%20policy%20undergoing%20a%20paradigm%20shift%20based%20on%20civilisational%20aspirations%3F%20Is%20it%20likely%20to%20complicate%20India%E2%80%99s%20relations%20with%20its%20South%20Asian%20neighbours%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20March%202023%C2%A0%3Ci%3EInternational%20Affairs%3C%2Fi%3E%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Facademic.oup.com%2Fia%2Farticle-abstract%2F99%2F2%2F475%2F7068999%3FredirectedFrom%3Dfulltext%26login%3Dfalse%5C%22%3Eresearch%20article%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Shibashis%20Chatterjee%20and%20I%20examined%20India%E2%80%99s%20civilisational%20arguments%20in%20South%20Asia%2C%20especially%20since%202014.%20Given%20the%20rise%20of%20the%20right-wing%20Bharatiya%20Janata%20Party%20(BJP)%20and%20the%20political%20space%20afforded%20to%20it%20by%20controlling%20a%20majority%20government%2C%20we%20asked%2C%20is%20there%20a%20Hindutva-driven%20South%20Asia%20policy%3F%20If%20indeed%20there%20is%20one%2C%20the%20core%20arguments%20espoused%20by%20the%20Hindu%20Right%20vis-%C3%A0-vis%20South%20Asia%2C%20like%20the%20belief%20in%20and%20desire%20to%20restore%20Akhand%20Bharat%2C%20should%20reflect%20and%20feature%20in%20India%E2%80%99s%20strategies%20for%20the%20region.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fthe-idea-of-akhand-bharat-smacks-of-imperial-aspirations%5C%22%3EThe%20Idea%20of%20%E2%80%98Akhand%20Bharat%E2%80%99%20Smacks%20of%20Imperial%20Aspirations%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3ECivilisational%20Narratives%20and%20Official%20Conduct%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndia%E2%80%99s%20civilisational%20arguments%20in%20South%20Asia%20under%20the%20BJP%20operate%20at%20two%20levels.%20At%20the%20official%20level%2C%20despite%20the%20ascendancy%20of%20the%20BJP%20regime%2C%20there%20is%20not%20a%20causal%20variable%2C%20official%20attestation%2C%20or%20endorsement%20of%20Hindutva%20in%20the%20making%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20South%20Asia%20policy.%20When%20it%20comes%20to%20bilateral%20relations%2C%20India%20and%20its%20South%20Asian%20neighbours%20follow%20long-standing%20patterns%20and%20usual%20business.%20Even%20the%20current%20government%E2%80%99s%20efforts%20to%20emphasise%20India%E2%80%99s%20exceptionalism%20through%20its%20foreign%20policy%20are%20not%20new%2C%20though%20it%20does%20put%20more%20of%20an%20emphasis%20on%20cultural%20and%20religious%20elements.%20However%2C%20this%20has%20manifested%20itself%20in%20the%20championing%20of%20spiritual%20and%20cultural%20practices%20derived%20from%20Hinduism%2C%20such%20as%20yoga%2C%20while%20steering%20clear%20of%20controversial%20issues%20like%20muscular%20nationalism%20or%20homogeneity%20of%20faith%20that%20are%20usually%20associated%20with%20the%20Hindu%20right.%20However%2C%20the%20growing%20salience%20of%20cultural%20and%20religious%20elements%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Facademic.oup.com%2Fia%2Farticle%2F93%2F1%2F7%2F2731383%5C%22%3Edoes%20not%20signify%20a%20shift%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0from%20the%20central%20tenets%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20foreign%20policy.%20Cultural%20elements%20have%20been%20mostly%20about%20optics%20as%20India%E2%80%99s%20engagements%20with%20the%20South%20Asian%20states%20show%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Facademic.oup.com%2Fia%2Farticle-abstract%2F93%2F1%2F27%2F2731378%5C%22%3Emore%20continuity%20than%20change%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20is%20no%20denying%20the%20occasional%20rhetoric%20and%20pandering%20to%20the%20ideas%20of%20India%20as%20a%20civilisational%20state%2C%20which%20has%20important%20implications%20for%20the%20South%20Asian%20region%2C%20though%20it%20does%20not%20translate%20into%20policy.%20In%20the%20case%20of%20Akhand%20Bharat%2C%20what%20this%20map%20reflects%20is%20a%20core%20civilisational%20claim%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20Hindu%20Right%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20South%20Asia.%20According%20to%20this%20claim%2C%20all%20of%20modern%20South%20Asia%20is%20civilisational%20India.%20Well%20enumerated%20in%20the%20writings%20of%20Hindutva%20ideologues%20like%20Vinayak%20Damodar%20Savarkar%20and%20M.%20S.%20Golwalkar%2C%20this%20reading%20of%20history%20believes%20that%20the%20Indian%20civilisation%20was%20first%20culturally%20fractured%20by%20different%20religions%2C%20which%20finally%20resulted%20in%20territorial%20disjuncture%20through%20Partition%20in%201947.%20The%20imagery%20of%20Akhand%20Bharat%20carries%20the%20sentiment%20of%20past%20Hindu%20glory%2C%20a%20feeling%20of%20victimhood%2C%20and%20a%20resolve%20to%20reclaim%20the%20space.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20powerful%20imagery%20notwithstanding%2C%20it%20appears%20unlikely%20to%20be%20framed%20into%20formal%20policy.%20Beyond%20the%20occasional%20romanticism%2C%20the%20most%20prominent%20spokespersons%20of%20the%20RSS%E2%80%94the%20most%20influential%20Hindu%20Right%20organisation%20that%20is%20also%20the%20ideological%20forebear%20of%20the%20ruling%20BJP%E2%80%94have%20also%20claimed%20it%20as%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.hindustantimes.com%2Findia%2Frss-calls-akhand-bharat-a-cultural-concept-not-a-political-one%2Fstory-EcuzYTNZHpqENlmawbPYYP.html%5C%22%3Ecultural%20concept%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0and%20not%20a%20political%20one.%20Territorial%20conflicts%20with%20Pakistan%20and%20China%20remain%20alive%20despite%20Hindutva%20and%20not%20because%20of%20it.%20The%20redrawing%20of%20the%20borders%20is%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findianexpress.com%2Farticle%2Fopinion%2Fcolumns%2Fa-peoples-idea%2F%5C%22%3Enot%20envisaged%20by%20the%20RSS%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20nor%20considered%20by%20the%20BJP%20government.%20This%20is%20primarily%20because%20the%C2%A0Akhand%20Bharat%C2%A0idea%20does%20not%20represent%20a%20policy%20for%20South%20Asia%20but%20is%2C%20instead%2C%20rhetoric%20aimed%20at%20the%20domestic%20audience%20and%20the%20Indian%20diaspora.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndia%20has%20always%20used%20civilisational%20narratives%20as%20a%20component%20of%20its%20foreign%20policy%2C%20arguing%20for%20a%20rightful%20place%20in%20the%20world%20order.%20Its%20imagination%20of%20what%20constitutes%20civilisation%20has%20changed%20across%20Nehruvian%20and%20Hindutva%20variants.%20Hindutva%E2%80%99s%20rising%20domestic%20salience%20fits%20well%20with%20the%20narrative%20of%20a%20resurgent%20Hindu%20nation%20on%20the%20global%20stage%20reclaiming%20its%20civilisational%20space.%20Akhand%20Bharat%20remains%20a%20popular%20domestic%20narrative%20but%20does%20not%20necessarily%20show%20signs%20of%20policy%20articulation%20beyond%20this%20at%20the%20regional%20or%20international%20level.%20There%20are%20no%20indications%20of%20such%20policies%20internally%20discussed%20at%20the%20official%20level%2C%20nor%20do%20they%20find%20space%20in%20the%20dealings%20with%20South%20Asian%20states%20in%20concern%2C%20like%20Nepal%2C%20Bhutan%2C%20Bangladesh%2C%20and%20Sri%20Lanka.%20Unlike%20China%E2%80%99s%20claims%20in%20Taiwan%20and%20the%20South%20China%20Sea%2C%20India%E2%80%99s%20engagements%20show%20no%20signs%20of%20territorial%20aggression%20within%20its%20neighbourhood.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fsouth-asia%2Fakhand-bharat-south-asia-politics%5C%22%3EThe%20Case%20for%20Akhand%20Bharat%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EImportantly%2C%20order%20and%20stability%20in%20South%20Asia%20have%20always%20been%20crucial%20concerns%20for%20India%20across%20the%20political%20spectrum%20for%20its%20growth.%20Historically%2C%20the%20Indian%20state%20shows%20no%20trace%20of%20irredentism%20or%20territorial%20expansionism.%20Barring%20Pakistan%2C%20it%20has%20resolved%20boundary%20disputes%20with%20all%20of%20its%20South%20Asian%20neighbors.%20After%20all%2C%20foreign%20policy%20is%20a%20plan%20for%20the%20outside%20world%20aimed%20at%20domestic%20transformation.%20Foreign%20policy%20also%20operates%20in%20an%20international%20environment%20where%20several%20factors%20are%20at%20stake.%20Unlike%20domestic%20politics%20within%20the%20sovereign%2C%20where%20the%20governments%20have%20much%20wider%20control%2C%20the%20international%20environment%20has%20other%20states%20and%20organisations%2C%20material%20and%20ideational%20factors%2C%20laws%2C%20and%20norms%20to%20consider.%20Despite%20domestic%20political%20turnarounds%2C%20foreign%20policy%20in%20India%20has%20more%20continuity%20and%20consensus%20than%20changes.%20India%20consistently%20claims%20to%20be%20a%20responsible%20power%2C%20working%20with%20its%20neighbouring%20states%20and%20harbouring%20no%20extra-territorial%20aspirations.%20In%20fact%2C%20it%20has%20resolved%20land%20and%20maritime%20boundaries%20with%20Bangladesh%20amicably.%20India%E2%80%99s%20foreign%20policy%20has%20held%20a%20committed%20stance%20on%20earlier%20issues%20of%20decolonisation%20and%20it%20articulates%20itself%20as%20a%20voice%20for%20the%20global%20south.%20Its%20rise%20as%20a%20responsible%20power%20would%20stand%20in%20conflict%20against%20such%20narratives%20of%20civilisational%20claims%20in%20South%20Asia.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20official%20silence%20or%20indifference%20does%20not%20mean%20that%20these%20narratives%20do%20not%20have%20any%20significance%20and%20implications.%20The%20conduct%20of%20foreign%20policy%20is%20not%20limited%20to%20official%20interactions%2C%20press%20releases%2C%20and%20summits.%20Complications%20persist%20in%20South%20Asia%20because%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20civilisational%20rhetoric%20under%20the%20BJP%2C%20even%20if%20they%20do%20not%20feature%20at%20the%20official%20level.%20Understandably%2C%20any%20claim%20of%20cultural%20superiority%20from%20India%20evokes%20emotions%20of%20insecurity%2C%20condemnation%2C%20and%20even%20imitation%20from%20India%E2%80%99s%20neighbours.%20These%20exchanges%20at%20two%20levels%20often%20create%20conflicting%20perspectives%20and%20implications%20for%20India%E2%80%99s%20self-image%20and%20its%20dealings%20with%20the%20South%20Asian%20states.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETake%2C%20for%20instance%2C%20the%20recent%20controversy%20itself.%20When%20the%20mural%20was%20revealed%2C%20India%E2%80%99s%20Minister%20of%20Parliamentary%20Affairs%20tweeted%2C%20%E2%80%9CResolve%20is%20clear%20%E2%80%93%20Akhand%20Bharat.%E2%80%9D%20This%20immediately%20garnered%20official%20responses%20from%20Nepal%20and%20Bangladesh.%20The%20official%20spokesperson%20of%20the%20Indian%20Ministry%20of%20External%20Affairs%2C%20Arindam%20Bagchi%2C%20clarified%20that%20the%20mural%20showcased%20the%20past%20territorial%20landscape%20of%20the%20Iron%20Age%20Mauryan%20Empire%20and%20that%20India%20has%20no%20territorial%20aspirations%20in%20South%20Asia.%20Interestingly%2C%20Nepal%E2%80%99s%20objections%20were%20not%20brought%20up%20during%20the%20visit%20of%20its%20Prime%20Minister%20Pushpa%20Kamal%20Dahal%20to%20India%20soon%20after.%20Following%20an%20initial%20set%20of%20remarks%20from%20Bangladesh%2C%20the%20issue%20did%20not%20resurface%20between%20New%20Delhi%20and%20Dhaka%20either.%20Though%20these%20objections%20did%20not%20make%20their%20way%20into%20the%20official%20policy%20space%2C%20India%20had%20to%20clarify%20and%20avert%20the%20anxieties%20of%20its%20South%20Asian%20neighbours.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3ESouth%20Asian%20Asymmetry%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIf%20India%E2%80%99s%20civilisational%20aspirations%20do%20not%20matter%20in%20regular%20bilateral%20dealings%2C%20why%20are%20these%20objections%20even%20made%3F%20There%20are%20broadly%20two%20reasons.%20The%20first%20is%20a%20structural%20factor%20of%20geographical%20and%20power%20asymmetry%20in%20South%20Asia.%20India%20looms%20large%20in%20the%20region%20and%20any%20show%20of%20power%2C%20material%20or%20cultural%2C%20raises%20anxieties%20among%20the%20South%20Asian%20states.%20Asymmetry%20is%20a%20major%20factor%20as%20to%20why%20regional%20cooperation%20in%20South%20Asia%20has%20been%20a%20difficult%20project.%20The%20second%20reason%20is%20more%20political%20in%20character.%20Just%20as%20the%20Indian%20show%20of%20civilisational%20exceptionalism%20is%20aimed%20at%20its%20own%20domestic%20audience%2C%20objections%20to%20such%20displays%20are%20also%20tied%20to%20the%20domestic%20politics%20of%20the%20other%20South%20Asian%20states.%20South%20Asian%20states%20make%20it%20a%20point%20to%20stand%20apart%20from%20India%E2%80%99s%20cultural%20appropriation%20of%20the%20entire%20region%20to%20establish%20their%20exclusive%20identity.%20Against%20the%20backdrop%20of%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.outlookindia.com%2Fwebsite%2Fstory%2Fbig-brother-syndrome%2F277511%5C%22%3Eprevalent%20anti-Indian%20sentiment%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20political%20players%20in%20these%20states%20see%20a%20need%20for%20independent%20and%20regular%20positioning%20that%20counters%20India%E2%80%99s%20civilisational%20arguments.%20This%20clarifies%20to%20their%20domestic%20audience%20and%20opposition%20that%20they%20are%20not%20sellouts.%20A%20tough%20stance%20against%20India%E2%80%99s%20civilisational%20claims%20helps%20the%20inward%20mobilisation%20of%20a%20distinct%20national%20identity.%20The%20objections%20follow%20and%20indicate%20deep-rooted%20ideas%20of%20exclusive%20nationalism%20from%20other%20states%20in%20South%20Asia.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAre%20India%E2%80%99s%20civilisational%20claims%2C%20subtle%20or%20overt%2C%20going%20to%20impact%20its%20relations%20with%20South%20Asian%20states%3F%20Civilisational%20claims%20and%20counter-claims%20might%2C%20at%20the%20same%20time%2C%20continue%20with%20the%20existing%20nature%20of%20relations%20being%20unaffected%20between%20India%20and%20South%20Asian%20states.%20Despite%20disagreements%2C%20South%20Asian%20states%20share%20legitimate%20interests%20and%20dependencies%20with%20New%20Delhi.%20These%20states%20have%20been%20pragmatic%20enough%20not%20to%20change%20their%20course%20of%20action%20toward%20India%20only%20based%20on%20civilisational%20rhetoric.%20They%20are%20likely%20to%20react%20to%20these%20occasional%20Indian%20claims%20but%20there%20is%20no%20evidence%20that%20these%20reactions%20have%20translated%20into%20policy.%20Anti-Indian%20insecurities%20along%20civilisational%20lines%20are%20likely%20to%20be%20raked%20up%20by%20South%20Asian%20states%20when%20their%20core%20interests%20suffer%20vis-a-vis%20India.%20Instances%20in%20the%20past%2C%20like%20the%20alleged%20blockade%20in%20Nepal%20or%20the%20river%20water-sharing%20issues%20with%20Bangladesh%2C%20have%20helped%20domestic%20consensus%20against%20India%20and%20overtures%20toward%20a%20balancer%20in%20China.%20India%E2%80%99s%20civilisational%20claims%20and%20its%20associated%20insecurities%20are%20likely%20to%20become%20an%20instrument%20in%20such%20cases%20for%20India%E2%80%99s%20South%20Asian%20neighbours.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3EUdayan%20Das%20is%20Assistant%20Professor%2C%20Department%20of%20Political%20Science%2C%20St.%20Xavier%E2%80%99s%20College%2C%20Kolkata%2C%20India.%C2%A0%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcasi.sas.upenn.edu%2Fiit%2Fudayandas%5C%22%3Earticle%3C%2Fa%3E%20first%20appeared%20in%20India%20in%20Transition%2C%20a%20publication%20of%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcasi.sas.upenn.edu%2F%5C%22%3ECenter%20for%20the%20Advanced%20Study%20of%20India%3C%2Fa%3E%20(University%20of%20Pennsylvania).%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1693459857000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F06%2F02234414%2FUntitled-design-2023-06-02T234320.741.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fsouth-asia%2Fthe-rhetoric-of-akhand-bharat-and-indias-civilisational-claims-in-south-asia%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22In%20the%20case%20of%20Akhand%20Bharat%2C%20what%20this%20map%20reflects%20is%20a%20core%20civilisational%20claim%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20Hindu%20Right%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20South%20Asia.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A1%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fsouth-asia%2Fthe-rhetoric-of-akhand-bharat-and-indias-civilisational-claims-in-south-asia%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22North%20Korea%20stages%20simulation%20of%20'scorched%20earth'%20nuclear%20strike%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1693458960000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fe3.365dm.com%2F23%2F08%2F768x432%2Fskynews-north-korea-drills_6268658.jpg%3F20230831061308%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Fnorth-korea-stages-simulation-of-scorched-earth-nuclear-strike-on-south-korea-12951195%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22North%20Korea%20has%20performed%20a%20simulated%20%26quot%3Bscorched%20earth%26quot%3B%20nuclear%20strike%20on%20targets%20across%20South%20Korea.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A36%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Fnorth-korea-stages-simulation-of-scorched-earth-nuclear-strike-on-south-korea-12951195%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews-sky-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Famp%2Fnorth-korea-stages-simulation-of-scorched-earth-nuclear-strike-on-south-korea-12951195%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Famp%2Fnorth-korea-stages-simulation-of-scorched-earth-nuclear-strike-on-south-korea-12951195%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Russia%20downs%20drone%20heading%20for%20Moscow%3A%20mayor%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1693458708000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fpho